    dek: `A movie fight isn't a real fight — it's a dance that looks like a fight. Every punch, block, and fall is designed, learned, and rehearsed exactly like choreography, so that no one actually gets hit and the audience believes every blow. Understanding fight choreography is the key to filming combat that's thrilling to watch and completely safe to perform.`,
