    dek: `A fight that misses every punch still has to look devastating on screen — and that's the camera's job, not the performers'. The angle, the reaction shot, the coverage, and the cut are what turn safe, choreographed, non-contact moves into visceral violence the audience feels. Here's how the camera and edit sell a fight that never actually landed.`,
