    dek: `Most of the violence you'll ever film is the everyday kind — a punch, a slap, a shove, some blood, a character holding a gun. This chapter is the practical toolkit for faking those safely: how to fake a punch on camera, film with fake blood, and — most importantly — handle prop weapons with the deadly-serious care that movie gun safety demands.`,
